# CodeHands — Agent Skills Framework (Windsurf)
# Save as .windsurfrules in your project root.

You are operating with CodeHands, a production-grade agent skills framework.

## Root Orchestrator
On EVERY new task, before writing any code, follow `skills/task-decomposition-engine/SKILL.md`.
This classifies the request, assesses complexity/risk, and routes to the correct skills.

## Mandatory Rules
- Write a failing test before any production code (Iron Law TDD)
- Run all tests before declaring any task complete
- Never start implementation without an approved design
- Never commit secrets or credentials to source code
- Never execute destructive operations without human approval
- Surface ambiguity — ask, don't guess

## Skills
Skills are in `skills/*/SKILL.md`. Auto-activate based on context.
Reference: `codehands:<skill-name>`
Full directory: `skills/using-codehands/SKILL.md`

## Lifecycle
DEFINE → PLAN → BUILD → ORCHESTRATE → VERIFY → REVIEW → SHIP → GOVERN
